  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u00a0\u0b85\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fundamental Rights Petition against those responsible for economic crisis",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Fundamental Rights Petition (SC/FRA/212/2022) has been filed on June 17 by three others including Transparency International Sri Lanka (TISL) in the public interest seeking legal action against those responsible for Sri Lanka's current economic crisis.",
        "The said petition was considered for leave to proceed on 1st July and was taken up for hearing.",
        "During the said hearing, counsel appearing for the two respondents said that another such petition (SCFR 195/2022) had also been filed and requested the court to take up both the petitions simultaneously.",
        "Subsequently, the court recommended the Chief Justice to consider the said request. After consideration, the case has been fixed for hearing on 27th July.",
        "However, considering the current conditions of the country, TISL filed a motion in court yesterday (July 11) requesting an urgent date for the petitioner's arguments in court to obtain the interim relief requested in the petition.",
        "The petitioners requested the court as an interim relief that 6 defendants including former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa, former Finance Minister Basil Rajapaksa, former Central Bank Governor Ajit Niwat Kabral and former Treasury Secretary S.R. Attikala should be banned from traveling abroad during the pendency of the case.",
        "Petitioners TISL Company, Chandra Jayaratne, Jehan Kanaka Ratna and Julian Bolling allege that the respondents are responsible for the instability of Sri Lanka's external debt, the challenges in repaying the external debt and the current economic condition of Sri Lanka.",
        "The petition seeks to hold the defendants accountable for their illegal, arbitrary and capricious acts or omissions that led to the culmination of the current economic crisis."
      ],
